com.example.rocketapp

Class DataManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.rocketapp.DataManager

  • public class DataManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Handles all interaction between the application and firestore. Keeps firestore synced user list, experiments list, and current user. Handles user login and account creation, and adding/modifying/deleting experiments, trials, and questions.

      • listen

        public static void listen(Experiment experiment,
                          DataManager.ExperimentCallback onUpdate)
        Listens to firestore for changes to this experiment. You MUST use this to get the trials and questions for an experiment. You may want to update the UI in onUpdate.
        Parameters:
        experiment - The experiment to listen to.
        onUpdate - Callback for implementing desired behaviour when the experiment is updated in firestore.
